gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Hawks 122, Rockets 113
gameRecap.excerpt: The Hawks defeated the Rockets, 122-113. Dejounte Murray led the way for the Hawks with 34 points, six rebounds and seven assists, while Saddiq Bey (24 points, six rebounds) and Trae Young (18 points, eight assists) added a combined 42 points in the victory. Jalen Green tallied 26 points, 14 rebounds and 10 assists for the Rockets in the losing effort, the first triple-double of his career. The Hawks improve to 24-29 on the season, while the Rockets fall to 23-29.
